# Implementation alignment

- Controllers orchestrate; **domain commands/services** own invariants. No GL line construction in controllers.
- Money movement must go through **`Core::Posting`** (or explicit commands that delegate to it), not ad-hoc balance updates.
- Use **transactions** at application boundaries where a business operation spans multiple writes; prefer DB constraints where appropriate.

## Tests (financial code)

- For posting/ledger/event flows, prefer tests that pin **invariants** (balanced legs, immutability, idempotency, reversal linkage) over only happy-path UI tests.
